In the United States, ''The Altar and the Door'' ranked as the 144th best-selling album and the fourth best-selling Christian album of 2007.<ref name="Year-end Billboard 200 (2007)" /><ref name="Year-end Christian Albums (2007)" /> It was the 95th best-selling album and best-selling Christian album of 2008<ref name="Year-end Billboard 200 (2008)" /><ref name="Year-end Christian Albums (2008)" /> and the 25th best-selling Christian album of 2009.<ref name="Year-end Christian Albums (2009)" /> ''The Altar and the Door'' was the 18th best-selling Christian album of the 2000s decade<ref name="Decade-end Christian Albums (2000s)" /> and has sold over 1,000,000 copies in the United States.<ref name="The Daily Times">{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailytimes.com/Weekend/story/Casting-Crowns-members-more-concerned-with-the-bigger-picture-than-sales-success-id-017992|title=Casting Crowns members more concerned with the bigger picture than sales success|last=Wildsmith|first=Steve|date=November 11, 2011|work=The Daily Times|publisher=Blount County Publishers LLC|accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>

==Singles==
Three singles were released from ''The Altar and the Door''. [[Lead single]] "[[East to West (song)|East to West]]" peaked at number one on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Christian Songs]] chart and spent nineteen weeks at the top spo, tied for the second-longest run at the number one spot in the history of the chart.<ref name="Ask Billboard">{{cite web|last=Trust|first=Gary|url=http://www.billboard.com/column-chartbeat/ask-billboard-which-carrie-songs-to-play-1004086196.story#/column-chartbeat/ask-billboard-which-carrie-songs-to-play-1004086196.story|title=Ask Billboard: Which Carrie Songs to 'Play'?|date=April 23, 2010|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref> It also peaked at number twenty-five on the ''Billboard'' [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles]] chart<ref name="Bubbling Under Hot 100" /> and ranked at number six on the decade-end Christian Songs chart.<ref name="Hot Christian Songs Decade-end (2000s)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/charts/decadeendcharts/2009/christian-songs|title=Hot Christian Songs Decade-end (2000s)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=13 October 2011}}</ref> The album's second single "[[Every Man]]", peaked at number two on the Christian Songs chart<ref name="Christian Songs (May 31, 2008)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2008-05-31|title=Christian Songs (May 31, 2008)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref> and at number one on the ''[[Radio & Records]]'' Soft AC/INSPO chart.<ref name="R&R Soft AC peak">{{cite web|title=Soft AC/INSPO National Airplay|last=Jessen|first=Wade|work=[[Radio & Records]]|accessdate=June 18, 2005|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080415100754/http://www.radioandrecords.com/Formats/Charts/Christ_Inspo_Chart.asp|archivedate=April 15, 2008}}</ref> "[[Slow Fade]]", the album's final single, peaked at number five on the Christian Songs chart.<ref name="Christian Songs (December 20, 2008)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2008-12-20|title=Christian Songs (December 20, 2008)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>

